{"title": "Astrochicken","content": <div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Astrophysical thought experiment by Freeman Dyson</div>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1320445320">.mw-parser-output .hatnote{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output div.hatnote{padding-left:1.6em;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .hatnote i{font-style:normal}.mw-parser-output .hatnote+link+.hatnote{margin-top:-0.5em}@media print{body.ns-0 .mw-parser-output .hatnote{display:none!important}}</style><div class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" role="note">This article is about the hypothetical self-replicating spacecraft concept. For the side game from Space Quest III, see .</div>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><figcaption>Freeman Dyson in 2005</figcaption></figure>
<p><b>Astrochicken</b> is the name given to a  expounded by  . An Astrochicken is a small, one-kilogram , a self-replicating  that could explore space more efficiently than a crewed craft could due to its innovative mix of technology.
</p>
